    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>COATS VIYELLA TO CUT JOBS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Coats Viyella Group PLC, Britain's biggest textile maker, will sell off clothing and other divisions and cut about 1,900 jobs and focus on its global threads business (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Coats Viyella Group P.L.C., Britain's biggest textile maker, with brands that include Van Heusen and Jaeger, said it would sell off clothing and other divisions and cut about 1,900 jobs, dealing a blow to the ailing British textile industry. The move follows a decision by Marks &amp; Spencer P.L.C., the largest British clothing retailer and Coats Viyella's biggest customer, to trim inventories as its business slumps. Coats Viyella said it would focus on its global threads business.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
